An Act improving the Massachusetts Department of Transportation project efficiency.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Notwithstanding any general or special law to the contrary, there shall be a
2 special commission to study and provide recommendations on improving the efficiency and
3 reducing the timeline for Massachusetts Department of Transportation projects. The commission
4 shall examine the current project planning, design, permitting, procurement, and construction
5 processes to identify inefficiencies and recommend best practices for streamlining project
6 delivery. The study shall include but not be limited to: (1) Reviewing MassDOTâ€™s internal
7 project management procedures; (2) Evaluating the permitting and approval processes across
8 state and local agencies; (3) Identifying regulatory or statutory barriers that contribute to project
9 delays; (4) Assessing the impact of project labor agreements and contractor procurement
10 methods on project timelines; (5) Comparing MassDOT project timelines with transportation
11 departments in other states with faster project delivery; (6) Exploring opportunities for public-
