12 private partnerships to accelerate project completion; (7) Recommending policy reforms or
13 statutory changes to improve project efficiency.
14 SECTION 2. The commission shall consist of the Secretary of Transportation or their
15 designee, who shall serve as chair; the Administrator of MassDOT Highway Division or their
16 designee; the State Auditor or their designee; the Attorney General or their designee; the House
17 Chair of the Joint Committee on Transportation or their designee; the Senate Chair of the Joint
18 Committee on Transportation or their designee; the House Minority Leader or a designee; the
19 Senate Minority Leader or a designee; one representative from the Massachusetts Municipal
20 Association; one representative from the Associated General Contractors of Massachusetts; and
21 two public members with expertise in transportation infrastructure, construction management, or
22 project delivery, appointed by the Governor.
23 The commission shall hold not fewer than four public hearings across different regions of
24 the Commonwealth to gather input from municipal leaders, industry professionals, and the
25 public.
26 SECTION 3. The commission shall submit its findings, along with any legislative or
27 regulatory recommendations, to the Governor, the Clerk of the House of Representatives, the
28 Clerk of the Senate, the Joint Committee on Transportation, and the House and Senate
29 Committees on Ways and Means no later than 12 months after the passage of this act.
